description:
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a motivated committed healthcare assistant to join our team. We are a 37 bed surgical ward caring for predominately vascular and urology patients.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must be a caring individual who can demonstrate a kind and compassionate approach to your work. We require an individual who is professional and presents themselves in a way that they can be looked up to as a role model. We continue to work and progress to be the best team we can be for our patients, their families and our community. We therefore welcome enthusiastic individuals to share and be part of our vision.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ward 26 is a supportive environment and we are committed to your professional development and learning. You will be supported as a new member of staff on our ward and mandatory as well as on ward training will be completed. We have a positive approach to our work and strive to provide the highest quality of patient care. You will work alongside qualified nurses, medical staff as part of a multidisciplinary team providing personal and all elements of care. Previous experience in caring would be an advantage as would NVQ study or the willingness to undertake this. But full training and induction will be given.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We look forward to welcoming you to ward 26.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name;  Rachel Woods&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title:  Ward Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address:  rachel.woods4@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
